PCInfo Classic compliance bundle
================================

This repository ships its own code under MIT, but generated images also
redistribute third-party software and data. The following files are intended
to travel with generated images:

  - LICENSE
  - THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES
  - BUNDLED_PACKAGES.tsv
  - SOURCE_LOCATIONS
  - SOURCE_OFFER
  - COPYING.GPL-2.0
  - COPYING.GPL-3.0
  - COPYING.LGPL-2.1
  - COPYING.APACHE-2.0
  - COPYING.BSD-3-Clause
  - NOTICE.APACHE-2.0
  - PATCHES/kexec-tools-binary-adjustment.txt

What this bundle does:

  - identifies the project's own license,
  - records which third-party components are bundled,
  - records the bundled Alpine package names, versions, origins, repos, and
    declared license expressions,
  - records Alpine package metadata/source-reference URLs,
  - records the local kexec-tools binary adjustment that affects source
    correspondence.

Important limitation:

This bundle improves redistribution readiness, but it is not a legal opinion
or an absolute guarantee. Some bundled packages use combined or alternative
license expressions, and exact compliance still depends on distributing the
matching corresponding source and any required notices for the exact binaries
you ship. The generated package/source reference files are intended to make
that review auditable, especially when package versions change.
